create_input_data

create_input_data.Rd

Creates input data set in correct format for use by other functions

Usage

create_input_data(
  vacc_data = list(),
  pop_data = list(),
  regions = c(),
  years = c()
)

Arguments

vacc_data

Data frame containing vaccination coverage data with region in column 1, year in column 2 and coverage values by age in remaining columns

pop_data

Data frame containing population data with region in column 1, year in column 2 and population values by age in remaining columns

regions

Vector of regions for which to extract data from vacc_data and pop_data (in alphabetical order)

years

Vector of years for which to extract data from vacc_data and pop_data '

Details

Takes in vaccination and population data in data frames (in columns by age with columns showing the region and year for each row), extracts number of age groups (verifying that this is the same in each data frame), extracts data for specified regions and years, and creates list in format used by other functions (vectors of region names, years and age groups, 3-dimensional arrays of vaccination and population data).
